    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\n**Bug:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts` — `processItems` uses `i < items.length - 1` instead of `i < items.length`, so the loop always stops one iteration early.\n\n**Fix:** A single character change on line 7 of `src/utils.ts`:\n\n```typescript\n// Before (buggy)\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {\n\n// After (fixed)\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n```\n\n**Impact:** 2 Vitest tests currently fail (`\"should process all items\"` and `\"should handle a single item\"`). After the fix, all tests will pass. No other files need to be touched.",
